These actions meet a critical need to provide the best support to the teams in various contexts:

+ During public health crises, when many actions have been focused on uncertainty management, resilience and remote work;

+ Upon returning to the workplace, in order to act responsibly in normalising hybrid work by implementing best practices in operations and communications;

+ During transformation projects, specifically in 2022, with the merger of Societe Generale Retail Banking and Credit du Nord, when psychosocial risk prevention measures were applied with the teams.

The focus areas are as follows:

+ Information and awareness actions with an educational purpose, for all company stakeholders;

Also, in 2023, psychosocial risk prevention initiatives were conducted, covering 97% of Societe Generale’s workforce, and included:

+ Training in psychosocial risk prevention for employees, managers, the HR line and Employee Representatives;

+ An annual employee survey including questions about conditions of life at work and stress levels in France. The various findings from the survey are used to establish corrective actions for the relevant teams.

